src/
======

Source only. Every subdirectory here holds just `.pdesc`/`.hdesc` sources
plus one Makefile -- no `.bin`/`.txt` output and no firmware blobs are
ever written here. Built output goes to the mirrored path under
../bin/ (see ../bin/README), so this tree stays clean
even right after a build.

Only three configs here are considered finished/canonical:
OpenSPARC_T1_rebuild/, t1_boot_fix/, tlb_fix/. Experimental/in-progress
variants (derived from one of these three, not yet promoted) live under
_test/, mirrored at ../bin/_test/ and ../patches/_test/.

OpenSPARC_T1_rebuild/1up/
    Sun's original, unmodified 2006 OpenSPARC T1 "niagara" sources
    (common.pdesc/common.hdesc/1up.pdesc/1up.hdesc, copied verbatim from
    ../bin/_reference/OpenSPARC_T1_original/niagara/). Building this
    proves our GNU-make-ported mdgen (github.com/unix0cc/mdbuild)
    reproduces Sun's shipped binaries byte-for-byte -- see
    ../bin/OpenSPARC_T1_rebuild/.

t1_boot_fix/256/1up/, t1_boot_fix/1024/
    The same original sources with the boot-fix patches from
    ../patches/t1_boot_fix/ applied (memory/cpus/cache nodes +
    mmu-page-size-list/mmu-#va-bits platform props -- the minimal set
    proven necessary for a clean sun4v boot on illumos/OpenSolaris
    t1_boot_fix, see docs/niagara-findings.md Experiment #16). 256/ and
    1024/ differ only in mblock.size (MD) / GUEST() memsize (hv-config),
    matching the intended QEMU -m value. 1024/ is flat (no "1up"
    subdirectory) since it's a single config; 256/ keeps the
    subdirectory-per-config convention shared with OpenSPARC_T1_rebuild/.

tlb_fix/1024, tlb_fix/2048, tlb_fix/4096
    t1_boot_fix plus one added per-cpu "tlb" node (see
    ../patches/tlb_fix/), fixing the sfmmu_cpu_init panic
    ("failed to get MMU CTX domain index") hit by Solaris 10u10+/
    Solaris 11 on the t1_boot_fix builds. Flat layout (no "1up"
    subdirectory) at every size.

Building
--------
    cd <config>/          # e.g. t1_boot_fix/256, t1_boot_fix/1024, OpenSPARC_T1_rebuild
    make                  # writes .bin/.txt + firmware symlinks into
                           # the mirrored ../../bin/<config>/ path
    make distclean         # removes that output, leaves source untouched

Each Makefile's `MDGEN` defaults to $(HOME)/mdbuild/bin/mdgen (built from
github.com/unix0cc/mdbuild, not part of this repo) and `FW_BLOBS` points
at ../../fw_blobs/ for the static OBP/firmware blobs symlinked alongside
each build's output.

Adding a new config
--------------------
Copy an existing config directory's Makefile, adjust OUT_DIR to the new
mirrored ../bin/<path> location, and drop in the .pdesc/.hdesc
sources (plus any patches, tracked in ../patches/).
